paragraphs: Especially if your kitchen is meant to be an open room connecting to other spaces, wood counters might be a great option. An important component of Scandinavian design, the warm colors give the room a soothing, inviting aura. Choosing the same wood for the countertop as for the dining table is smart in many contexts. This creates a room concept with self-sufficiency. Choosing wood for a workstation or tabletop depends critically on the material being treated extensively before to use. A properly oiled wood countertop may be cleaned almost as easily as a ceramic one. Still, be advised that especially rustic wood needs to be re-oiled after few years to retain its quality. Moreover, you have to use cleaning agents designed especially for wood only.
